      <div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">
      </div>
      <h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">
        <i>
          Book of Ingenious Devices
        </i>
      </h1>
      <div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
        <div id="siteSub" class="noprint">
          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
        </div>
        <div id="contentSub">
        </div>
        <div id="jump-to-nav">
        </div>
        <a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">
          Jump to navigation
        </a>
        <a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">
          Jump to search
        </a>
        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
          <div class="mw-parser-output">
            <div class="thumb tright">
              <div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;">
                <a href="/wiki/File:Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg" class="image">
                  <img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg/220px-Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="264" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg/330px-Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg/440px-Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg 2x" data-file-width="456" data-file-height="548"/>
                </a>
                <div class="thumbcaption">
                  <div class="magnify">
                    <a href="/wiki/File:Banu_musa_mechanical.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge">
                    </a>
                  </div>
                  Drawing of 
                  <i>
                    Self trimming lamp
                  </i>
                   in 
                  <a href="/wiki/Ahmad_ibn_M%C5%ABs%C4%81_ibn_Sh%C4%81kir" class="mw-redirect" title="Ahmad ibn Mūsā ibn Shākir">
                    Ahmad ibn Mūsā ibn Shākir
                  </a>
                  's treatise on  mechanical devices. The manuscript was written in 
                  <a href="/wiki/Arabic" title="Arabic">
                    Arabic
                  </a>
                  .
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>
              The 
              <i>
                <b>
                  Book of Ingenious Devices
                </b>
              </i>
               (
              <a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">
                Arabic
              </a>
              : كتاب الحيل 
              <i>
                Kitab al-Hiyal
              </i>
              , 
              <a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">
                Persian
              </a>
              : كتاب ترفندها 
              <i>
                Ketab tarfandha
              </i>
              , literally: "The Book of Tricks") was a large illustrated work on 
              <a href="/wiki/Mechanical_device" class="mw-redirect" title="Mechanical device">
                mechanical devices
              </a>
              , including 
              <a href="/wiki/Automaton" title="Automaton">
                automata
              </a>
              , published in 850 by the three brothers of 
              <a href="/wiki/Persian_people" class="mw-redirect" title="Persian people">
                Persian
              </a>
              <sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference">
                <a href="#cite_note-1">
                  [1]
                </a>
              </sup>
               descent, known as the 
              <a href="/wiki/Banu_Musa" class="mw-redirect" title="Banu Musa">
                Banu Musa
              </a>
               (Ahmad, Muhammad and Hasan bin Musa ibn Shakir) working at the 
              <a href="/wiki/House_of_Wisdom" title="House of Wisdom">
                House of Wisdom
              </a>
               (
              <i>
                Bayt al-Hikma
              </i>
              ) in 
              <a href="/wiki/Baghdad" title="Baghdad">
                Baghdad
              </a>
              , 
              <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">
                Iraq
              </a>
              , under the 
              <a href="/wiki/Abbasid_Caliphate" title="Abbasid Caliphate">
                Abbasid Caliphate
              </a>
              .
              <sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference">
                <a href="#cite_note-2">
                  [2]
                </a>
              </sup>
               The book described about one hundred devices and how to use them.
              <sup id="cite_ref-Hill-44_3-0" class="reference">
                <a href="#cite_note-Hill-44-3">
                  [3]
                </a>
              </sup>
            </p>
            <div id="toc" class="toc">
              <input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" value="on"/>
